 MONTHS_BETWEEN() :- 
 ------------------------------------

  => returns no of months between two dates 

		MONTHS_BETWEEN(DATE1,DATE2)

Ex :- 

   SELECT  MONTHS_BETWEEN(SYSDATE,'12-FEB-2025') FROM DUAL ;    =>   12
              
 
  => display  ENAME   EXPERIENCE  in months ?

       SELECT  ename, FLOOR(MONTHS_BETWEEN(SYSDATE,hiredate))  as expr  FROM emp ; 
    
	smith             541
	allen             539

   => display   ENAME   EXPERIENCE  ?
                                      M  YEARS  N MONTHS 

          experience =  40  months  = 3 years 4 months 
 
          years   =   months / 12   = FLOOR( 40 / 12 )  = 3
           
          months =  MOD(months,12) = MOD(40,12) = 4 

          SELECT  ename, 
                          FLOOR ( MONTHS_BETWEEN(SYSDATE,hiredate)/12)  as years,
                          MOD(FLOOR(MONTHS_BETWEEN(SYSDATE,hiredate)) , 12)  as months
          FROM emp ; 
    
 
          smith    17-DEC-80                    17-DEC-2025          45 YEARS   
                                                             17-JAN-2026           1  MONTH

 LAST_DAY() :- 
 -------------------

   => returns last day of the month 

                         LAST_DAY(date)

 Ex :- 

  SELECT LAST_DAY(SYSDATE)  FROM  DUAL  ; 	=>  28-FEB-26
            
 => waq to display first day of the next month ?

 SELECT LAST_DAY(SYSDATE)  + 1  FROM  DUAL  ;    =>  01-MAR-26	

  => waq to display current month 1st day ? 

   SELECT ADD_MONTHS ( LAST_DAY(SYSDATE)  + 1 ,-1)  FROM  DUAL  ;  => 01-FEB-26 

 NEXT_DAY() :- 
 --------------------

  => returns next day from given date

             NEXT_DAY(DATE, DAY)

Ex :- 

 SELECT NEXT_DAY(SYSDATE,'SUNDAY')  FROM DUAL ;    =>   15-FEB-26 

 => waq to print next month 1st sunday ?

     SELECT     NEXT_DAY ( LAST_DAY(SYSDATE) , 'SUNDAY')   FROM DUAL ; 
    
  => waq to print current month last sunday ?

   SELECT     NEXT_DAY ( LAST_DAY(SYSDATE) , 'SUNDAY')  - 7  FROM DUAL ; 

Queries :- 

 1  waq to print 1st day of the next month ?
 2  waq to print last day of the current month ?
 3  waq to print 1st day of the current year  ?
 4  waq to print 1st day of the next year ?
 5  waq to print last day of the current year ?

Conversion :- 
--------------------

 => conversion means converting one datatype to another datatype
 => conversion is 2 types 

 1  implicit conversion
 2  explicit conversion

 implicit conversion :- 
 -----------------------------

  =>  conversion performed by oracle then it is called implicit conversion

Ex 1 :- 

  SQL>SELECT   5000 +  '1000'     FROM DUAL ;      =>      6000

   for the above query string  '1000'  converted to number by oracle

Ex 2 :- 

  SQL>CREATE TABLE   D(D    DATE);

   SQL>INSERT INTO D VALUES('01-JAN-26');

   for the above query string '01-JAN-26' converted to date by oracle

  NOTE :- 

   => some times implicit conversion fails 

Ex :-

  SQL>SELECT  5000 + '1,000'  FROM DUAL ;  => ERROR

  SQL>INSERT INTO D VALUES('01/12/26') ;  => ERROR

 Explicit Conversion :-
 ------------------------------

 =>  if conversion performed by user then it is called explicit conversion
 =>  the following functions provided by oracle to do explicit conversion
 
  1  TO_CHAR	=>  converts date / number to char  
  2  TO_DATE           =>  convers string to date
  3  TO_NUMBER     =>  convers string to number

  converting date to char type :-
  -----------------------------------------
  
 => dates converted to char type to display dates in different formats 
 
                TO_CHAR(DATE , 'format')  

   FORMATS :-           TO_CHAR(SYSDATE,'format')
   ------------------
 
     YYYY				2026			
     YY				26
     YEAR				TWNETY-TWENTY SIX
     CC				21  (centuary)
